ani','Anandji Veerji Shah, Kalyanji Veerji Shah',NULL,NULL),('Patita',8,'Radha earns a living begging in order to support herself and her crippled and ailing father. They live in a small tenament, under the constant threat of eviction by their landlord for unpaid rent for several months. One day, while begging, Radha meets a young man, Nirmal Chander, who would like to see her improve her status by getting employment, he even goes to the extent of assisting her find work in a mill. He subsequently invites her over to meet his mother, and asks her to marry him, to which she agrees. Nirmal also seeks the permission of her dad. When he goes to get her to make arrangements for their marriage, he finds her and her dad gone. His attempts to locate her are in vain. Then after several months he finds her living in a small dilapidated hut with a young man named Mastram and a child - she calls her own - but claims that she is unmarried. Who is the biological father of this child? Where is he located?',143,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTYxMDQ1NDU0NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNzcxNDE0MQ@@.jpg',1953,'Drama','Hindi','Amiya Chakrabarty','Chandrakant, Rajendra Shankar','Amiya Chakrabarty','Minoo Katrak, Jaikishan Dayabhai Panchal, Shankarsingh Raghuwanshi','V. Babasaheb','D.B. Joshi'),('Jyoti Bane Jwala',4.9,'Suraj and Malti are in love and get very intimate. They are introduced to their respective families, and there is approval all round, and their marriage is to be finalized soon. Before that could happen, Suraj meets with an accident and is killed instantly, leaving Malti devastated. Malti\'s dad, Charandas, is shocked to find that Malti is pregnant, and both of them re-locate to a secluded area, where Malti\'s gives brith to a baby boy. Charandas has the child disposed off in a garbage can, and tells Malti that the child died. Malti recovers and subseqeuntly marries Mr. O.P. Bakshi, and settles down. Years later, while watching a dance show with her husband, Malti sees a young man who resembles her husband in every shape and form. She attempts to make inquiries, but is afraid of what her husband will think when he finds out that the young man is her son, born out of marriage. The young man is Jyoti, who was left in a garbage can at the time of his birth, but is now a dreaded, ruthless, and much feared criminal don, going by the name of Jwala.',166,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDUxMjcxNDktYWM1NC00YTc3LTljZTMtYjY2MDZiNTgwMmFhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyOTIzODUxMjk@.jpg',1980,'Drama, Family, Action','Hindi','Dasari Narayana Rao',NULL,'Prasan Kapoor','Laxmikant Shantaram Kudalkar, Pyarelal Ramprasad Sharma',NULL,NULL),('Dada',4.2,'A bloody vendetta spans generations and leaves no member of the involved clans untouched.',125,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjIxNzU4OTE4MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTk4Mzg1MDI@.jpg',2005,'Thriller','Bangla',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),('Janki',NULL,'Panaji based Shreeram Sawant is an honest and hardworking person who lives with his wife Janki his mother and daughter Uma he gets promoted due to hard work which makes fellow worker Janardhan jealous leading a tiff between the two where Shreeram passes away.His family shifts to Mumbai but find that the place they have come to live does not exist anymore Halwadar Tukaram comes to their rescue and takes the family along with him and they share a good bonding.Janki who has become a widow at young age is eyed by their landlord Dharmappa but she ignores his advances and decides to live a decent life.Few years later their family condition isn\'t good Uma who loves Mahesh son of Tukaram and has talent of singing and dancing decides to pursue her talent for surgery of her grandmother where a big businessman tries to molest her but gets saved by his trusted aide whose none other then Shreeram.Shreeram is very much alive an faked his death he finds that Uma is his daughter after he hears Janki singing but decides to stay away from them as he has taken to world of crime